  <content>
    <description>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>NAME</title>
        <para>s1kd-acronyms - Generate a list of acronyms from S1000D data modules</para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>SYNOPSIS</title>
        <para>
          <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs24" changeType="modify" reasonForUpdateRefIds="rfu-0001">s1kd-acronyms [-dfptxh?] [-n &lt;#&gt;] [-T &lt;types&gt;]
              [-m &lt;acronyms&gt;] [-o &lt;file&gt;]
              [&lt;datamodules&gt;]</verbatimText>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <para>The <emphasis>s1kd-acronyms</emphasis> tool generates a list of unique acronyms used in S1000D data modules. It can also mark up acronyms in data modules automatically based on an existing list.</para>
      </levelledPara>
      <levelledPara>
        <title>OPTIONS</title>
        <para>
          <definitionList>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-d</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Format XML output as an S1000D <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs12">&lt;definitionList&gt;</verbatimText>.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem changeType="add" reasonForUpdateRefIds="rfu-0001">
              <listItemTerm>-f</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>When marking up acronyms with the -m option, overwrite the input data modules instead of writing to stdout.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-h -?</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Show help/usage message.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-i -I</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Markup acronyms in interactive mode. If the specified acronyms list contains multiple definitions for a given acronym term, the tool will prompt the user with the context in which the acronym is used and present a list of the definitions for them to choose from.</para>
                <para>When not in interactive mode, the first definition found will be used.</para>
                <para>The -I option prompts for all acronyms, not just those with multiple definitions. This can be useful if some occurrences of the acronym term should be ignored.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-m &lt;acronyms&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Instead of listing acronyms, automatically markup acronyms given in the &lt;acronyms&gt; XML file in the specified data modules. Occurrences of the acronym term will be replaced in text with the <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs12">acronym</verbatimText> element in the list.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-n &lt;#&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Minimum number of spaces after the term in pretty-printed text output.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-o &lt;file&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para changeType="modify" reasonForUpdateRefIds="rfu-0001">Output to &lt;file&gt; instead of stdout.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-p</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para changeType="modify" reasonForUpdateRefIds="rfu-0001">Pretty print text/XML acronym list output.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-T &lt;types&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Only search for acronyms with an attribute <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs13">acronymType</verbatimText> whose value is contained within the string &lt;types&gt;.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-t</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Format XML output as an S1000D <verbatimText verbatimStyle="vs12">&lt;table&gt;</verbatimText>.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>-x</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Use XML output instead of plain text.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
            <definitionListItem>
              <listItemTerm>&lt;datamodules&gt;</listItemTerm>
              <listItemDefinition>
                <para>Data modules to find acronyms in.</para>
              </listItemDefinition>
            </definitionListItem>
          </definitionList>
        </para>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
